e, Euclide, Henri, Hilaire, Huguette.","Altered form of French   Touchet  , reflecting the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>."]}]},{"name":"James","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name borne in the New Testament by two of Christ's disciples, James son of Zebedee and James son of Alphaeus. This form comes from Late Latin <i>Iacomus</i>, a variant of <i>Iacobus</i>, Latin form of Greek <i>Iakobos</i>. This is the same name as Old Testament   Jacob   (Hebrew <i>Yaakov</i>), but for many centuries now they have been thought of in the English-speaking world as two distinct names. In Britain, <i>James</i> is a royal name that from the beginning of the 15th century onwards was associated particularly with the Scottish house of Stewart:  James I  of Scotland (  1394–1437 ; ruled  1424–37 ) was a patron of the arts and a noted poet, as well as an energetic ruler.  King James VI  of Scotland (  1566–1625 ; reigned  1567–1625 ) succeeded to the throne of England in  1603 . His grandson,  James II  of England (  1633–1701 ; reigned  1685–8 ) was a Roman Catholic, deposed in  1688  in favour of his Protestant daughter Mary and her husband William of Orange. From then on he, his son (also called James), and his grandson Charles (‘Bonnie Prince Charlie’) made various unsuccessful attempts to recover the English throne. Their supporters were known as Jacobites (from Latin <i>Iacobus</i>), and the name James became for a while particularly associated with Roman Catholicism on the one hand, and Highland opposition to the English government on the other. Nevertheless, it has since become one of the most perennially popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"James Touchet was born about 1250, in Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs. James Touchet about 1273, in Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"ABT 1250–":"umbes 1250–Surnud","1255–Female":"1255–Surnud","1275–1300":"1275–1300","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","ABT 1250":"umbes 1250","ABT 1273":"umbes 1273","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1275":"1275","1250":"1250","Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Frankton, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Welsh,Frankton,Shropshire,England":"Frankton, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1250–":"noin 1250–Kuollut","1255–Female":"1255–Kuollut","1275–1300":"1275–1300","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","ABT 1250":"noin 1250","ABT 1273":"noin 1273","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1275":"1275","1250":"1250","Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Frankton, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Welsh,Frankton,Shropshire,England":"Frankton, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1250–":"environ 1250–Décédé","1255–Female":"1255–Décédée","1275–1300":"1275–1300","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","ABT 1250":"environ 1250","ABT 1273":"environ 1273","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1275":"1275","1250":"1250","Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Frankton, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Welsh,Frankton,Shropshire,England":"Frankton, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"James Touchet est né environ 1250, à Frankton, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Mrs. James Touchet environ 1273, à Frankton, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"ABT 1250–":"um 1250–Verstorben","1255–Female":"1255–Verstorben","1275–1300":"1275–1300","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","ABT 1250":"um 1250","ABT 1273":"um 1273","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1275":"1275","1250":"1250","Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Welsh,Frankton,Shropshire,England":"Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"James Touchet wurde um 1250 in Frankton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom gebore